source.Name: Total population
source.Summary: Population: Total population and distribution by age and sex estimated to be consistent with the population by age and sex of the (a) 1950, 1976, 1992, 2001, 2012 censuses; (b) adjusted for under/over count; (c) adjusted for age heaping; (d) adjusted for under enumeration of children under age 15; (e) official estimates through 2023; and with estimates of the subsequent trends in fertility, mortality and international migration.

source.Name: Total fertility rate
source.Summary: Fertility: Total fertility rate and age pattern of fertility based on: (a) birth-histories data from the 1980 EDN and 1989, 1994, 1998, 2003, 2008, 2016 DHS; (b) adjusted fertility using Brass P/F ratio method (or variants) with data on children ever born and births in the preceding 12 (or 24/36) months, both classified by age of mother, from the 1976, 1992, 2001, 2012 censuses and 1980 EDN; (c) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1980 EDN and 1992, 2001 censuses; (d) cohort-completed fertility backdated by the mean age of childbearing from the 1976, 2001 censuses and 1989, 1994, 1998, 2003, 2008 DHS; (e) International estimates considered up to 2019. In addition, the (a) official estimates of age-specific fertility rates through 2019; (b) registered births classified by age of mother and the underlying female population by age through 2019; (c) adjusted for underregistration; (d) birth-histories data from the 1975 EDN; (e) births in the household in the preceding 12 (or 24) months classified by age of mother from the 1976, 1992, 2001, 2012 censuses; (f) adjusted fertility using Brass P/F ratio method (or variants) with data on children ever born and births in the preceding 12 (or 24/36) months, both classified by age of mother, from the 1975 EDN; (g) indirect estimates obtained using Mortara's method with data on children ever born by age of mother from the 2002 PESMM; (h) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1950, 1976, 2012 censuses and 1955-2011 Education Stats and 2000 MICS; (i) cohort-completed fertility backdated by the mean age of childbearing from the 1988 ENPV and 1992, 2012 censuses and 2000 MICS have been considered.

source.Name: Life expectancy at birth
source.Summary: Overall Mortality: Life expectancy at birth and age pattern of mortality based on: (a) official estimates through 2010; (b) registered deaths by age and sex available through 2021; (c) adjusted for underreporting of infant and child deaths; (d) adult deaths adjusted for underregistration using death distribution methods; (e) mortality rates for older ages were adjusted; (f) estimates using LogQuad model life tables and estimates of infant and under-five mortality (5q0), and adult mortality (45q15).

source.Name: Age Mortality
source.Summary: Adult and Old Age Mortality: Estimates derived from: (a) deaths by age and sex available from Register through 2021; (b) adjusted for underregistration; (c) recent household deaths data by age and sex from the 1980 EDN; (d) recent household deaths adjusted at adult ages for underregistration using death distribution methods; (e) siblings deaths from the 1994, 2003, 2008 DHS; (f) maternal orphanhood from the 1980 EDN and 1994, 1998, 2003, 2008 DHS and 2000 MICS; (g) indirect estimates of male adult mortality based on female widowhood data from the 1980 EDN; (h) indirect estimates of female adult mortality based on male widowhood data from the 1980 EDN; (i) intercensal survivorship from successive census age distributions; (j) International estimates used up to 2021; (k) estimates of under-five, adult and old age mortality. In addition, the (a) recent household deaths data by age and sex from the 1992, 2001, 2012 censuses; (b) recent household deaths adjusted at adult ages for underregistration using death distribution methods; (c) maternal orphanhood from the 1975 EDN and 1988 ENPV; (d) paternal orphanhood from the 1980 EDN and 1988 ENPV and 1994, 1998, 2003, 2008 DHS and 2000 MICS; (e) indirect estimates of male adult mortality based on female widowhood data from the 1975 EDN and 1976, 1992, 2001, 2012 censuses and 1989 EIH and 1989, 1994, 1998, 2003, 2008, 2016 DHS and 2000 MICS; (f) indirect estimates of female adult mortality based on male widowhood data from the 1975 EDN and 1976, 1992, 2001, 2012 censuses and 1998, 2003, 2008 DHS and 2000 MICS; (g) intercensal survivorship from successive census age distributions have been considered.

source.Name: Infant/child mortality
source.Summary: Child Mortality: Under-five mortality based on: (a) official estimates of infant and child mortality through 2017; (b) registered infant and child deaths through 2021; (c) direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 1989, 1994, 1998, 2003, 2008, 2016 DHS; (d) indirect estimates from data on children ever born and surviving from the 1975, 1980 EDN and 1976, 2001, 2012 censuses and 1988 ENPV and 2000 MICS; (e) recent household deaths from the 1980 EDN and 2012 Census; (f) International estimates used up to 2021. In addition, the (a) indirect estimates from data on children ever born and surviving from the 1992 Census; (b) recent household deaths from the 1992, 2001 censuses have been considered.

source.Name: International migration
source.Summary: Migration: International migration based on: (a) information on foreign-born populations from censuses and registers from major countries of destination; (b) estimates derived as the differences between overall population growth and natural increase; (c) UNHCR statistics on the number of refugees in the main countries of asylum.
